      <abstract>
        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>WHAT?</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                Key changes in the &suselinux;&nbsp;16 migration include replacing &yast; with
                &agama;, shifting from Service Packs to annual releases and adopting Wayland over
                X11. This version mandates 64-bit architectures while fully removing legacy support
                for &xen; (PV), <systemitem>wicked</systemitem> and SysV init scripts.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>WHY?</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                Use this guide to plan your transition from &slea;&nbsp;15 to &suselinux;&nbsp;16
                by understanding these foundational technical shifts.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>EFFORT</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                It takes approximately 20 minutes to read the article.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>GOAL</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                Assess migration impact and adapt your infrastructure to the new
                &suselinux;&nbsp;16 standards.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
      </abstract>
